of the public sector and enroll our children who will be the leaders of the next generation in private schools where the teachers and staff are held accountable by the parents and strive to teach our children with a passion that has been lost in the public schools since tenure has taken over and the young passionate teachers have been set to the side.  But have no fear, the private sector will snatch up the good ones they have turned away and  they will succeed for years to come with the joy of being able to teach and care about each child while the public schools continue to battle union contracts and loss of quality teachers.  Maybe then they will notice their flaws, stop blaming the private schools for taking the children out of the crappy schools and understand they need to fix their misguided ways.  I went to public school, but we did the Pledge of Allegiance with &quot;one nation under God&quot;, not the edited version for the few.  I am proud that 99% of the comments on here are about our children's well being and education and that we will not &quot;Dumb Down&quot; our children because we choose to send them to get a private education. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1449" language="en" documentId="2962" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Gulfcaptain" date="Aug 29, 2013 7:58PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="11" thumbsDown="0" origId="2962" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1449"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>